hey i'm having a weird issue with my shopify theme. on mobile the product image is overlapping the title text like it's just sitting right on top of it. i tried changing the margin but it didn't do anything. here is my css snippet for the product header:

.product-header {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  padding: 20px;
}

.product-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}

.product-title {
  font-size: 24px;
  margin-top: 10px;
}

any idea why it's overlapping on small screens?

Ah, it sounds like your product image is taking up too much space on the mobile screen, causing it to overlap the title text. You might want to consider using a smaller image or adjusting the width of the image to better fit the screen. You could also try adding a max-width property to the product image to ensure it doesn't exceed a certain width. Here's an example:

```css
.product-image {
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}
```

This should help prevent the image from taking up too much space and overlapping the title text on smaller screens. Remember, it's always a good idea to test your changes on different devices to make sure they look good on all screen sizes. Good luck with your Shopify theme!
